events.description: The release of Malta's industrial output data for December 2025, showing a 6% year-on-year decline.

facts.fact_text: Malta's industrial production fell by 6% year-on-year in December 2025.

evidences.evidence_text: Malta’s industrial production fell by 6% year-on-year in December 2025

facts.fact_text: Energy production grew by 8.7% in December compared to 3.7% in the previous month.

evidences.evidence_text: gains were recorded in energy production (8.7% vs 3.7%)

facts.fact_text: Capital goods activity rebounded to 4.4% from a 7.1% decline.

evidences.evidence_text: activity rebounded in capital goods (4.4% vs -7.1%)

facts.fact_text: On a seasonally adjusted monthly basis, industrial activity grew by 4.2% in December.

evidences.evidence_text: On a seasonally adjusted monthly basis, industrial activity grew by 4.2% in December, recovering from a 0.1% fall in November.

claims.claim_text: The slowdown in the industrial production decline was primarily caused by improved output in manufacturing.

evidences.evidence_text: The slowdown was mainly driven by higher output in the manufacturing sector (-7% vs -9%)

evidence.evidence_text: The slowdown was mainly driven by higher output in the manufacturing sector (-7% vs -9%)
Across main industrial groupings, gains were recorded in energy production (8.7% vs 3.7%)
On the other hand, activity fell further in consumer non-durable goods (-6.9% versus -2.8%)
